God can use a crooked stick to draw a straight line. God used Driscoll in my life when I needed it. I don’t know If he was legit or if he was using shallow tactics, but I know The Holy Spirit convicted me when I heard him. God used Balam’s donkey he can use anyone to speak through. I’m thankful God was merciful to me a sinner and saved me.

🤘🏼😆🤘🏼 Mark D at his hype!

I attended a few months to MarsHill in Bellevue, WA and believe me in spite of his downfall, God used this man’s ministry to bring me (and more than one individual) to his fold and made feel the power of his redemptive grace... which made my roots grow even deeper in the Gospel. 
So before casting stones for Mark Driscoll, one should check him self first and see how not so sinless he is... plus too many highly profile biblical figures did horrible deeds before or after they answered God’s call. The apostles betrayed and abandoned Jesus. Paul was a murderer an a notorious enemy of the faith. David was murderer and an adulterer. Salomon drenched in adultery and idolatry. Jonas was a racist and a rebel. Noah was a drunk... and many more. And yet they are part of God’s glory through the ages of his word by His grace alone. 
Mark is a man of God... he needs Jesus and got reminded of who is really in charge of the church. This does not diminish in any way the harm he did and the forgiveness he’s had (or still has) to beg to Christ sheep.
Preach! What a powerful truth! @markdriscoll

@eve_meets_mary so what do you say about the Apostle Paul who before he was chosen by JESUS, he was persecuting followers of JESUS? Oh how about Peter who denied even knowing JESUS and was cussing while being asked if he knew JESUS? Let’s go way back and ask why David was told by GOD, even after he committed adultery and murder, that the Savior would come through bloodline?? C’mon now!!!! Just cuz PMD sinned (have you never sinned) doesn’t mean GOD can’t use him. Perhaps you should put your faith in GOD and not in men. Let GOD do HIS will and stop condemning the people who are just as flawed as me and you when they sin. We are all sinners and JESUS is the only perfect one...have faith in the PERFECT ONE.

Just like most of the prophets and kings in the Bible, PMD is flawed...but remember GOD uses the least among us to bring us back to HIM. Listen to PMD’s message before you spew out your dislike of him. #glorytogod
Thank you pastor Mark 👏🏽👏🏽👏🏽
